result.execSummary:
The defendant Francisco Villanueva was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

miscConds.notes: Restitution in the amount of $730.81 has been paid to, and disbursed by, the Clerk of Circuit Court to the victims as outlined in the Restitution Summary filed with the Court on January 22, 2016.  The 10% surcharge in the amount of $73.08 remains due and owing as part of the costs imposed.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with the victims A. Banda and/or P. Banda as named in the Complaint.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

Case Called @ 3:55 PM: Defendant Francisco Villanueva in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at a previous hearing today.  Per DA:  Agreement conditioned upon the payment of Restitution up front - Def had made a payment today of $684.89.  State qualifies Restitution owed - as to this case $730.81, outstanding balance of $45.92.  Def expected to plead  NC to Ct 1 Battery.  Ct 2 & Ct 3 to be DRI.   Argued terms on sentencing.  State recites probationary sentence with conditions.  Victims present in Court today and may wish to speak.  Per Atty Zamzow - balance of restitution will be paid following the hearing today.  Def confirms resolution reached.    Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed - both victims present with their son that will be able to aid with statements they wish to make.  Plea Ct 1 - Battery: NC   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Count Nos 2 and 3 both DRI.  Son (Alejandro) makes a statement on behalf of his parents prior to sentencing.  Argument by DA as to penalty - argues for period of probation as of today, it is believed that Def intends to reside in Wisconsin for the next year - State makes no affirmation or commitment as to Def's ability to transfer to the State of Utah.  Argument by Atty Zamzow as to penalty - states Def will reside with relatives in Milwaukee.  DOC advised her that Def could pay a $150 deposit to petition for a transfer to the State of Utah which could take up to 8 mos to arrange and may be denied.  Request early termination be ordered on probation.  Defendant would request 30 days to travel to Utah to cancel the lease and pack up belongings.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  Accepts resolution - 5 mos WCJ - I/S (GT, Huber and No TS credit) - S/W - 1 yr probation.  Conditions:    The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; Rest of $730.81 recognizing that $684.89 has already been paid, balance to be paid no later than 9/1/2016, any unpaid Rest ordered converted to civil judgment in favor of victim; Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP; DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.   Defendant must report to DOC by the end of the week here in Wautoma.  No contact with victims - PB or AB.  Court does not authorize early termination of supervision.  Appeal Rights Given.
